<b><i>Table 9</i> – NV Index bits</b>

Note: HMAC U/S, Device Key U/S -- U/S stands for Unique String.

Note: All NV index profiles now include OWNERWRITE=1 and OWNERREAD=1.
This enables the Owner hierarchy to read and write FDO credential
data after successful onboarding (TO2), supporting credential reuse,
key rotation, and decommissioning. Pre-onboarding credential integrity
is provided by the TPM's key protections (fixedTPM, non-exportable)
and the HMAC binding between credentials and the Ownership Voucher,
not by NV index access restrictions. Provisioning entities that
require stricter pre-onboarding access control MAY set OWNERWRITE=0
and OWNERREAD=0 with an appropriate authValue, but SHOULD plan for
how post-onboarding credential management will be accomplished.

